<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,310,403,429]" box="[189,310,403,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,403,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,403,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,1399,450,728]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Head and pronotum yellowish-orange; remainder of mesosoma black; metasoma orange; wings blackish with a pale subapical patch; face sparsely punctate and moderately protruding dorsally; clypeus smooth, with median subapical tubercle moderate, ventral margin truncate; frons laterally smooth, medially transversely striate, with two submedian carinae diverging toward lateral ocelli; antenna with 36 flagellomeres; mesopleuron with epicnemial 
<taxonomicName box="[721,793,590,616]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="carina">carina</taxonomicName>
reaching level of mesopleural pit; subtegular ridge convex; fore wing with 2m–cu slightly apical to rs–m; tergite 1 stout in female (male unknown); tergites 1–3 smooth, following tergites moderately punctate with basal transverse striations; apical margins of all tergites straight. CT 2.0; ML 0.6; POL 1.3; OOL 1.6; Fl 
<subScript attach="left" box="[877,886,714,728]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">1</subScript>
3.6; Fl 
<subScript attach="left" box="[967,984,714,728]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">15</subScript>
2.1; FL 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1077,1094,714,728]" fontSize="6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">33</subScript>
0.9; T1 1.3; OT 4.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,457,761,787]" box="[189,457,761,787]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,761,787]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,761,787]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,1399,808,905]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">A species with unique color pattern, with most of mesosoma black, metasoma orange and wings blackish with a subapical light patch; otherwise characterized by the sparsely punctate face, the truncate ventral margin of the clypeus and the stout tergite 1 of the female.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,324,944,970]" box="[189,324,944,970]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,944,970]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
